I love this place! The rice balls are very good and they package it very well for travel . Park on the street or there are public parking lots. I really like the mushroom and unagi. 3 Rice ball combo is a great deal.
The rice balls are great! You can't go wrong with any of the flavors, but my favorite are the beef, teriyaki chicken, and curry chicken.

Awesome place for a quick bite! Love the quick service. Bulgogi is sooo good, literally KBBQ in a ball lol. I also love their spam musubi and California roll too. Will be back to try the different flavors for sure :)

Wow! A great find in a huge row of food available. This is more of a quick fix shop. I highly recommend the shrimp & beef onigiri (rice ball). The salmon is overcooked and underwhelming. The tamago (egg) is okay.

Awesome spot, I wish there was a spot like this where I live in Glendora. My favorites are the chicken curry and beef teriyaki so far. Can't wait to try the others! Would def come back! THEY HAVE MUSUBI AS WELL!!!!

This place is unquestionably one of the most pleasant place to eat in the region. Whenever I come to this place I am truly pleased. They maintain their high  standard service and the topmost level of dishes  they give. You can never go wrong with this restaurant. Very  recommended.

An onigiri shop in Glendale, yes please!!! Delicious, filling, artisan onigiri that comes out quick and fresh.  There are many types to choose from and after the first two, I will be back to try out MOST of the rest.  And they seem to have two interesting specials available, but the price wasnt clearly given so I didn't go for it

The. Best. Onigiri. I. Have. Had. Period. Anyone going through the Americana Mall owes it to themselves to check this restaurant out. They won't be disappointed!!
Always a pleasure walking in here

I really enjoy this place since the rice balls are delicious and filling despite their size. My favorite order is three chicken teriyaki riceballs with edamame. It doesn't take that long either for the order to be ready. Even takeout is fast and they wrap and label each riceball.
Fast, cheap, yet so delicious. If I lived closer I’d be a regular
Great food at a really reasonable price. I've been going here consistently for about 3 or 4 years now. Personal favorite of mine. Lots of different options for the rice balls too.

I love this place! If I lived closer, I would be here at least once a week. I have not tried all of the rice balls yet but so far my favorites are the spicy shrimp and the crab meat. I have also really enjoyed the avocado roll. The rice …

I love this place. I wish there were more locations. I drive all the way from Covina to visit. All of their flavors are delicious. I've never had a disappointing visit to Gam Tu Bop. Everything literally taste great.
Done well! Taste good with brown rice also.

Amazing food at incredibly low low prices! Such a lovely family run local business. The owner told me that the name Gam Tu Bop came from that moment in time when say a student comes home to Mom to visit and Mom gives him/her a big heap of rice and all the best food as a feast to show her love! ❤️
I love it..great price..simple and yummy.

Really tasty onigiri for an extremely affordable price. Wife and I ate for $14 and we are stuffed. Tried chicken curry and unagi - only downside is the furikaki is a little too salty and I def felt the sodium afterwards (with miso soup as well) so keep that in mind! Otherwise, stellar rice balls!

Can't beat the price. Can't beat the rice balls. Great for a quick economically feasible snack  :-)

This place is clean, the food is cheap, yummy, and filling, and the staff is always friendly. I love the udon and you can't go wrong with any of the rice balls! There usually isn't too much of a wait. It is a great place to grab a quick lunch if you work in the area or are shopping nearby at the Americana or the Galleria.

Eating a 🍚 tuna rice ball at Gam Tu Bop was the highlight of my trip to LA. Seriously.  Of all the food I ate, that rice ball was most memorable. I feel like getting on a plane right now to go have another.

Great Place. Been here several times and they never disappoint.

Prett good onigiri and miso soup. Our favorite spot is Sunny Blue on the westside but if you cant/don't want to take a trip to Santa Monica & Culver City this spot will do. And it's cheaper, too. The staff is great. We will definitely be back.
Visiting from NM, and this has been our favorite place to eat. Must try.

So delicious, so cheap! Truly a gem. I’ve been here several times, and have never been disappointed with the rice balls or the service. Get the spicy shrimp! Three rice balls are really filling, though two rice balls are usually enough.

Riceballs are great

Fast food style musubi. Not as good as the musubi cart that's around some farmers markets in LA (main problem was that a few rice balls of all that we tried fell apart really easily and nori was on the side), but still delicious and filling for the price.  Their beef rice ball is delicious!

Good place for a quick bite to eat.  The selection of balls is pretty good and varied. My favorite is the spicy shrimp, and the bulgogi is also good.  I was a little disappointed by the unagi as I found it a little too fatty for my liking, but I've enjoyed everything else I've had!
Amazing! It was very filling, healthy, cheap, and very very good. The food is well seasoned too. I recommend the beef and spicy shrimp rice ball. Also the miso soup is very good.
A delightful, clean restaurant with delicious food and friendly staff! A welcome change from the usual fare. Highly recommended.
I love this place.  I always get combo#2 - 2 Rice Balls (tuna) with Miso Soup.  Service is great.

Nice change from all of the burgers and kabobs, simple Korean rice balls and a couple of cup bop's they also have salads and noodles. I tried the beef cup bop and spicy shrimp rice ball, my significant other ordered the Gam Tu Bop#1 which comes your choice of three rice balls, pickeld ginger and edamame.
Excellent food and service
Bulgogi is great, can't go wrong with three rice bowls or a plate!
Flavorful, made-to-order rice balls.  Nice, friendly staff.
Really was craving a rice ball, found this place. Was so good, pretty cheap too.
Tasty rice balls in an unassuming spot in Glendale. The seasoning they use for the rice is a great balance of savory and sweet.

Amazing and affordable little restaurant!  Normally as a vegetarian it's really difficult being able to find meatless rice balls but this place has changed that!
